    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Family containing around 30,000 species of beetles characterized as being stout-bodied, having bright metallic colors, clubbed antennae, and front legs are broad and adapted for digging. The family includes the scarab, species Scarabaeus sacer, considered sacred in ancient Egypt.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
